{
  "texts": [
    "However, reading the endogenous factors correctly proves difficult.",
    "The reason is that it is always complicated to conceptualize a future phenomenon before it has materialized.",
    "For example, it is hard to conceive of a process to explain a new technology like an Internet browser to a person who has never seen a computer.",
    "Yet, forecasting is supposed to be easier than is generally anticipated.",
    "81 In this regard, imagination expressed through, for example, science fiction and other oxymora or paradoxes, can provide useful insights for law and how to actively design the future by regulating it."
  ]
}